      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MEPUNGA WHISKEY (1) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a strong early split last time, paving the way for a 0.8 lengths win at Sandown over 515m in 29.87. Was a winner at his only start from this draw. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. PAW BRUTUS (6) was in the money two back in a Grade 5 at this track then jumped from a squeeze draw last time and was not far away when second (30.36) over 525m at this track. Key player on best and worth another try. RIPPED PAIGE (3) led all the way last time out to score by 4 lengths (30.07) at this track in a Grade 5 over 525m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Leading chance again. BLACKPOOL WINTER (5) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish.",
